{"id": "EUVD-2025-28971", "enisaUuid": "1c4b3df9-f6cb-3cb3-b4b5-ba72a6187bf6", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\ndrm/xe/migrate: prevent potential UAF\n\nIf we hit the error path, the previous fence (if there is one) has\nalready been put() prior to this, so doing a fence_wait could lead to\nUAF. Tweak the flow to do to the put() until after we do the wait.\n\n(cherry picked from commit 9b7ca35ed28fe5fad86e9d9c24ebd1271e4c9c3e)", "datePublished": "2025-09-11T18:35:50", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-25T21:32:04", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/7e46fa64a4b94208563c3a5bf1d7f4346f94abea", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/145832fbdd17b1d77ffd6cdd1642259e101d1b7e", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-39740"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-39740"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "239dfa7e-bb7b-3758-8457-a7a078e349fd", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.17-rc2"}, {"id": "667761d2-4f78-3d75-9941-3695bbf1687f", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6.16"}, {"id": "8959b7af-0dc3-327b-8a39-b04a9acf0bf0", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "270172f64b114451876c1b68912653e72ab99f38 <7e46fa64a4b94208563c3a5bf1d7f4346f94abea"}, {"id": "9fa5ea6b-0da6-3087-bbff-81b8bacff53b", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "270172f64b114451876c1b68912653e72ab99f38 <145832fbdd17b1d77ffd6cdd1642259e101d1b7e"}, {"id": "e3d235e4-348d-3b5a-83b4-bc8fa4ffeba2", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.16.2"}, {"id": "e5317c16-46bb-36f3-a988-b4287cfa1527", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.17"}, {"id": "fe4fca82-e508-3b47-af9b-2b11a308e16f", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "859b898a-4e84-3840-b8f4-6ed39d69ac1e", "vendor": {"name": "Linux"}}], "isExploited": false}